The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence and other education leaders during a roundtable discussion on reopening schools in South Carolina amid the COVID-19 pandemic. Pence expressed support for Governor Henry McMaster's decision to return students to school after Labor Day and emphasized the importance of reopening schools for the well-being of students and working families. He highlighted the low risk the virus poses to young people and the negative consequences of keeping children out of school. Pence also mentioned the resources and funding that have been allocated to education efforts, as well as the upcoming release of additional guidance on safely reopening schools. The Second Lady, Karen Pence, also spoke about the challenges faced by teachers, parents, and students during remote learning and the importance of returning to in-person education. The transcript concludes with Pence expressing gratitude to all the participants and assuring them of the administration's support.